	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2983888233" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2983888233" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hey Johan!</p><p>This is a question that people ask from time-to-time, because it's different than you see in other frameworks. Long story short, you can (of course) do it either way :). It's done this way because (A) [as you correctly mentioned] it helps reduce boilerplate duplications and (B) [more importantly] when I originally helped write the official Symfony documentation, I chose to do it this way... and so everyone has been doing it this way ever since :). I still think it's the best way... but there's no huge reason why you should choose one vs the other.</p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
