	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2747489407" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2747489407" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>I'm glad you dislike the duplication actually :). There are 2 basic approaches to this:</p><p>A) Create your own BaseController class (that itself extends Symfony's Controller) and add any helper methods that you want inside of there. You can add whatever methods you want to cut-down on the boilerplate of the forms code.</p><p>B) Do the same basic thing, but put the code in some outside service. These are often called "Form handlers" - I don't do this approach, but a lot of people do.</p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
	                </li>
